 a

)a Minister may present a list of bills proposed to be referred to the Main Committee or other committees and (if at least 7 days have elapsed since the first readings of all of the bills) move without notice either immediately or at a later time "That the bills be referred to committee(s) in accordance with the list"; and

(

 b

)the bills referred to the Main Committee may be considered by it after details of the reference have been published in the Notice Paper.

